# Frontend API Services

## API Client Architecture

The API layer uses Axios with interceptors for authentication and token refresh.

### Client Configuration (`client.js`)

```javascript
import axios from 'axios';

const API_BASE_URL = '/api';
export { API_BASE_URL };

const api = axios.create({
  baseURL: API_BASE_URL,
  headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' }
});
```

### Request Interceptor (Auth Token)

```javascript
api.interceptors.request.use((config) => {
  const token = localStorage.getItem('access_token');
  if (token) {
    config.headers.Authorization = `Bearer ${token}`;
  }
  return config;
});
```

### Response Interceptor (Token Refresh)

```javascript
api.interceptors.response.use(
  (response) => response,
  async (error) => {
    if (error.response?.status === 401 && !originalRequest._retry) {
      originalRequest._retry = true;
      
      const refreshToken = localStorage.getItem('refresh_token');
      if (refreshToken) {
        const response = await api.post('/auth/refresh', { refresh_token: refreshToken });
        localStorage.setItem('access_token', response.data.access_token);
        
        // Retry original request with new token
        originalRequest.headers.Authorization = `Bearer ${response.data.access_token}`;
        return api(originalRequest);
      }
    }
    return Promise.reject(error);
  }
);
```

## API Module Structure

### Barrel Exports (`index.js`)

All APIs are exported from a central barrel file:

```javascript
// Named exports for direct imports
export { assetAPI, domainAPI, ipAPI, urlAPI } from './assets';
export { nucleiAPI, typosquatAPI } from './findings';
export { workflowAPI, scheduledJobsAPI } from './workflows';
export { authAPI, userManagementAPI } from './admin';
export { programAPI } from './programs';

// Default export for backward compatibility
export default {
  auth: authAPI,
  assets: { domains: domainAPI, ips: ipAPI, urls: urlAPI },
  findings: { nuclei: nucleiAPI, typosquat: typosquatAPI },
  workflows: workflowAPI,
  programs: programAPI
};
```

### Import Patterns

```javascript
// Preferred: Named imports
import { domainAPI, urlAPI } from '../services/api';
import { workflowAPI, programAPI } from '../services/api';

// Alternative: Default import (backward compatible)
import apiObject from '../services/api';
apiObject.auth.login(username, password);
```

## Asset APIs (`assets.js`)

### Standard CRUD Pattern

Each asset type follows a consistent pattern:

```javascript
export const domainAPI = {
  // Search with typed parameters
  searchSubdomains: async (params = {}) => {
    // params: { search, apex_domain, wildcard, has_ips, sort_by, sort_dir, page, page_size }
    const response = await api.post('/assets/subdomain/search', params);
    return response.data;
  },

  // Get by ID
  getById: async (id) => {
    const response = await api.get('/assets/subdomain', { params: { id } });
    if (response.data?.data) return response.data.data;
    throw new Error('Domain not found');
  },

  // Get by unique field (name, URL, etc.)
  getByName: async (domainName) => {
    const response = await api.get(`/assets/subdomain/name/${encodeURIComponent(domainName)}`);
    if (response.data.status === 'success') return response.data.data;
    throw new Error('Domain not found');
  },

  // Update notes
  updateNotes: async (domainId, notes) => {
    const response = await api.put(`/assets/subdomain/${domainId}/notes`, { notes });
    return response.data;
  },

  // Delete single
  delete: async (domainId) => {
    const response = await api.delete(`/assets/subdomain/${domainId}`);
    return response.data;
  },

  // Batch delete
  deleteBatch: async (domainIds, options = {}) => {
    const response = await api.delete('/assets/subdomain/batch', {
      data: { asset_ids: domainIds, ...options }
    });
    return response.data;
  },

  // Import
  import: async (domains, options = {}) => {
    const response = await api.post('/assets/subdomain/import', { domains, ...options });
    return response.data;
  },

  // Get distinct values for filtering
  getDistinctValues: async (fieldName, program = undefined) => {
    const body = program ? { program } : {};
    const response = await api.post(`/assets/subdomain/distinct/${fieldName}`, body);
    return response.data;
  }
};
```

### Available Asset APIs

| API | Endpoint Prefix | Key Methods |
|-----|-----------------|-------------|
| `domainAPI` | `/assets/subdomain` | `searchSubdomains`, `getById`, `getByName`, `updateNotes`, `delete` |
| `apexDomainAPI` | `/assets/apex-domain` | `search`, `getById`, `import`, `delete` |
| `ipAPI` | `/assets/ip` | `searchIPs`, `getByAddress`, `getById`, `updateNotes`, `delete` |
